Remove assemblies

Source: R/removeAssemblies.R
removeAssemblies.Rd

Exclude assemblies that were listed for removal for some reason.

Usage

removeAssemblies(x, file = NULL)

Arguments

x

A data frame or a matrix.

file

A tab-separated file (pattern, reason) listing assemblies to remove.

Value

The x object where genomes matching the patterns in file have been removed. For convenience, x is returned unmodified if file is NULL.

Author

Charles Plessy

Examples

removeAssemblies(Halo_PercentDiff, textConnection("Halobacterium_\ttest"))
